WEBVTT

1
00:03:54.500 --> 00:03:56.414
Range me.

2
00:03:59.109 --> 00:04:01.066
Three to five on the legs.

3
00:04:11.546 --> 00:04:13.459
They're coming.

4
00:04:32.069 --> 00:04:34.070
Scan him. Find Cabrera.

5
00:04:43.723 --> 00:04:46.723
At the jeep. Designer sunglasses.

6
00:04:46.766 --> 00:04:48.420
You sure that's him?

7
00:04:48.506 --> 00:04:50.593
I'm reading his rank and name tag.

8
00:04:53.419 --> 00:04:54.855
He's moving.

9
00:04:58.856 --> 00:05:01.246
Six-five-zero. Range me.

10
00:05:03.986 --> 00:05:06.638
Range correct: 6-5-0.

11
00:05:06.726 --> 00:05:09.596
When he clears the civilians.
he's mine.

12
00:07:16.175 --> 00:07:18.175
- Anything?
- No. nothing.

13
00:07:35.308 --> 00:07:37.134
Two more hours.

14
00:07:37.221 --> 00:07:39.178
Damn! I hate the down time.

15
00:07:39.265 --> 00:07:41.612
Well. you have a leave coming up.
don't you?

16
00:07:41.700 --> 00:07:43.482
Yeah.

17
00:07:57.311 --> 00:07:58.963
That can't be our extraction!

18
00:08:02.181 --> 00:08:05.615
Oh. those dipshits!
I told them no daylight!

19
00:08:05.703 --> 00:08:07.616
Should I pop smoke?

20
00:08:08.747 --> 00:08:12.748
Let's get out of here before those dicks
page us over the P.A. system!

21
00:10:07.065 --> 00:10:09.021
Come on!

22
00:10:22.674 --> 00:10:25.588
Get back! You're crazy!
He's gone down!

23
00:10:25.632 --> 00:10:27.023
Wait!

24
00:11:30.466 --> 00:11:33.205
Why didn't you let the door gunner
sweep it out first?

25
00:11:35.118 --> 00:11:38.248
My spotter's dead because you assholes
got here early!

26
00:11:38.336 --> 00:11:40.554
I asked for a night extraction!

27
00:11:40.641 --> 00:11:43.815
I ought to leave you out there.
you son of a bitch!

28
00:12:02.904 --> 00:12:05.208
We'll be needing both of those. gunny.

29
00:12:05.295 --> 00:12:06.948
He only needs one.

30
00:13:27.783 --> 00:13:29.741
Colonel Weymuth. this is Richard Miller.

31
00:13:29.784 --> 00:13:31.914
- He'll be our man in Panama.
- How do you do?

32
00:13:32.001 --> 00:13:35.393
- Heard a lot about you.
- Come on. Sit down.

33
00:13:52.438 --> 00:13:55.396
Intelligence indicates that there's
a major coup planned...

34
00:13:55.482 --> 00:13:57.265
for election day in Panama.

35
00:13:57.309 --> 00:14:01.569
Colombian drug lord Raoul Ochoa
is bankrolling it.

36
00:14:01.657 --> 00:14:05.744
His plan is to put in
rebel General Miguel Alvarez in power.

37
00:14:05.831 --> 00:14:08.874
We have less than one week
to prevent that.

38
00:14:08.918 --> 00:14:10.875
With his man Alvarez running
the country...

39
00:14:10.919 --> 00:14:13.963
Ochoa could very easily gain access
to the Panama Canal.

40
00:14:14.050 --> 00:14:16.701
We have only one shot at Alvarez...

41
00:14:16.789 --> 00:14:20.703
and it is absolutely critical
that we eliminate the general...

42
00:14:20.789 --> 00:14:22.616
prior to next week's election.

43
00:14:22.702 --> 00:14:28.139
Now. this operation
won't bear congressional scrutiny.

44
00:14:28.182 --> 00:14:31.268
It must be completely covert.

45
00:14:31.312 --> 00:14:34.312
You won't be getting a medal for this.

46
00:14:34.356 --> 00:14:36.878
But there will be other
tangible benefits.

47
00:14:36.965 --> 00:14:39.574
First one's Alvarez.

48
00:14:42.052 --> 00:14:44.184
Most recent photo
was taken ten days ago.

49
00:14:44.226 --> 00:14:46.532
The ponytail's Ochoa.

50
00:14:46.619 --> 00:14:49.705
Ochoa's never seen outside of Colombia.

51
00:14:49.793 --> 00:14:53.880
That's Alvarez's hacienda.
That's where you'll find him.

52
00:14:53.967 --> 00:14:55.489
That's your shooter.

53
00:14:57.446 --> 00:14:59.141
That's Master Gunnery Sargent
Thomas Beckett.

54
00:14:59.185 --> 00:15:01.012
He's the Marine Corps' top man.

55
00:15:01.055 --> 00:15:04.098
He's logged more time in the jungle
than any other sniper.

56
00:15:04.185 --> 00:15:07.490
On this particular mission.
your function is to be his spotter.

57
00:15:07.577 --> 00:15:11.055
Mr. Miller. should anything happen
to Beckett...

58
00:15:11.143 --> 00:15:13.404
your duty would be to eliminate Alvarez.

59
00:15:13.491 --> 00:15:16.404
- Personally.
- Don't worry about having to shoot him.

60
00:15:16.492 --> 00:15:19.449
Beckett is the best.
and I'm sure it wouldn't come to that.

61
00:15:19.536 --> 00:15:22.057
I may not have any kills...

62
00:15:23.144 --> 00:15:25.188
but I have had men in my sights.

63
00:15:25.275 --> 00:15:26.667
Good.

64
00:15:27.753 --> 00:15:31.233
We're giving you rank on this one:
GS-9.

65
00:15:31.319 --> 00:15:34.754
The mission is under your command.
It's your responsibility.

66
00:15:35.755 --> 00:15:37.015
Good luck.

67
00:15:38.190 --> 00:15:40.886
Consider it done. Gentlemen.

68
00:15:48.582 --> 00:15:50.060
One last thing.

69
00:15:50.148 --> 00:15:51.930
This assignment is critical.

70
00:15:52.018 --> 00:15:54.974
If at any point Beckett becomes
a liability...

71
00:15:55.061 --> 00:15:57.800
or he endangers this mission's
covert status...

72
00:15:58.887 --> 00:16:00.757
you're gonna have to take him out.

73
00:17:01.547 --> 00:17:04.417
The embassy's pleased.

74
00:17:04.459 --> 00:17:09.417
They'll mark Cabrera confirmed kill.
classified. on your service jacket.

75
00:17:09.505 --> 00:17:11.548
We're very sorry about your spotter.

76
00:17:11.591 --> 00:17:15.243
If was a rebel sniper that got Papich.
He's still out there.

77
00:17:18.679 --> 00:17:22.332
Washington is really excited
about these upcoming elections.

78
00:17:22.375 --> 00:17:24.897
Oh? Why is that. sir?

79
00:17:24.941 --> 00:17:27.985
Our policy is to see this country
have a freely-elected government.

80
00:17:28.072 --> 00:17:30.202
That could happen in a couple of months.

81
00:17:33.725 --> 00:17:36.334
You know it'll be the usual damn thing.

82
00:17:36.420 --> 00:17:38.813
People will be too scared to vote.

83
00:17:40.203 --> 00:17:43.203
Well. whatever you and I
may think. Tom...

84
00:17:43.291 --> 00:17:47.509
Washington feels that this is the right
time to go after the rebel leadership.

85
00:17:48.640 --> 00:17:51.248
You're sending it my way. sir?

86
00:17:51.335 --> 00:17:53.380
Yes. I am.

87
00:17:53.466 --> 00:17:57.249
We're getting a little long in the tooth
for this kind of thing. Tom.

88
00:17:57.336 --> 00:18:02.250
But I figured that this would make
a great capper for a fine career.

89
00:18:03.815 --> 00:18:07.989
The National Security Council is sending
a guy along to help- a shooter.

90
00:18:08.077 --> 00:18:11.555
- He's coming with full plans.
- A civilian?

91
00:18:11.642 --> 00:18:14.208
Just hold on.
Take a look.

92
00:18:14.295 --> 00:18:17.424
The army shooting team
plucked this guy right out of ROTC.

93
00:18:17.512 --> 00:18:19.773
He took a silver in the '88 Olympics.

94
00:18:19.861 --> 00:18:23.860
After his discharge the N.S.C. assigned
him to a Washington D.C. SWAT team.

95
00:18:23.948 --> 00:18:25.905
It's all in there.
Take a look.

96
00:18:27.817 --> 00:18:29.601
Has he ever been in a jungle?

97
00:18:29.688 --> 00:18:31.384
Does he speak any Spanish?

98
00:18:31.470 --> 00:18:34.775
This is not a matter of choice.
Just trust me.

99
00:18:34.818 --> 00:18:38.253
Anybody the N.S.C. sends down here
is gonna be fully qualified.

100
00:18:54.560 --> 00:18:56.603
Hey. yo!

101
00:18:56.691 --> 00:18:58.865
What do you got in there anyway?

102
00:19:00.560 --> 00:19:01.996
A bassoon.

103
00:19:04.822 --> 00:19:06.996
With the Marine Corps band. right?

104
00:19:07.083 --> 00:19:08.954
Exactly.

105
00:19:08.997 --> 00:19:12.780
New Psy-ops strategy. We're gonna
charm the rebels. like snakes.

106
00:19:13.911 --> 00:19:15.562
Whip a charm on this!

107
00:19:16.693 --> 00:19:18.649
Shit. Ripoly! Whip a charm!

108
00:19:25.476 --> 00:19:28.129
Hey. take a swig.

109
00:19:28.216 --> 00:19:31.129
It'll burn through that frost you got.

110
00:19:38.783 --> 00:19:40.434
Give me your battle dressing!

111
00:19:42.218 --> 00:19:44.826
Jesus Christ!

112
00:19:47.914 --> 00:19:50.088
We got wounded!

113
00:19:55.393 --> 00:19:57.133
Jesus Christ!

114
00:19:59.306 --> 00:20:01.176
Baker. stand by!

115
00:20:05.959 --> 00:20:07.307
We're hit!

116
00:20:16.699 --> 00:20:18.701
Where is he? Anyone got a visual?

117
00:20:21.135 --> 00:20:22.961
There he is! Get him!

118
00:20:28.048 --> 00:20:31.136
- He's on your side! Get him!
- You're gonna get us all killed!

119
00:20:31.223 --> 00:20:34.615
For Christ's sake! Take it down!

120
00:20:34.702 --> 00:20:37.137
- He's shooting at us!
- Use your fucking weapons!

121
00:20:39.050 --> 00:20:40.790
What the-

122
00:20:43.007 --> 00:20:47.573
We're gonna die!
Oh. God! We're gonna die!

123
00:20:56.705 --> 00:20:58.966
Kill him!

124
00:21:00.704 --> 00:21:03.706
Get us out of here!
Come on! Shoot him!

125
00:21:06.792 --> 00:21:09.576
Hit him! Come on! Go!

126
00:21:13.446 --> 00:21:15.359
Come on!

127
00:21:36.057 --> 00:21:38.274
Jesus Christ! You got him
with a sniper rifle!

128
00:21:39.840 --> 00:21:41.275
Yeah.

129
00:22:22.149 --> 00:22:25.715
- How about a game?
- I got a game.

130
00:22:32.976 --> 00:22:35.107
- Can I get a beer?
- Coming up.

131
00:22:38.890 --> 00:22:41.369
So you're going down south
towards the border.

132
00:22:42.499 --> 00:22:45.022
I'm not at liberty
to discuss my mission.

133
00:22:45.108 --> 00:22:48.152
How do you feel
about hanging on a charm bracelet?

134
00:22:50.804 --> 00:22:52.239
Come again?

135
00:22:52.327 --> 00:22:55.849
You better take a good look
at Master Beckett's dog tag collection.

136
00:22:55.936 --> 00:22:58.066
Got any money?

137
00:23:00.849 --> 00:23:02.763
Yeah. I'll play for money.

138
00:23:07.980 --> 00:23:10.112
I said I already got a game.

139
00:23:13.590 --> 00:23:15.981
I'm talking about holding on
to your cash...

140
00:23:16.025 --> 00:23:18.155
while you're out in the jungle.

141
00:23:20.198 --> 00:23:21.635
Better do it.

142
00:23:21.678 --> 00:23:26.243
Those rebels can fund a whole offensive
on what they take off you.

143
00:23:29.287 --> 00:23:33.288
I'm ready for a game now.

144
00:23:34.374 --> 00:23:36.114
He doesn't have time for a game.

145
00:23:38.462 --> 00:23:39.767
GS-9 Miller?

146
00:23:56.551 --> 00:23:58.508
A lot of attitude around here.

147
00:23:58.595 --> 00:24:01.986
Welcome to "Marine World."
Those people thought you were a sniper.

148
00:24:02.074 --> 00:24:03.987
It's an outcast profession.

149
00:24:05.204 --> 00:24:07.205
They always go out in platoon strength.

150
00:24:08.248 --> 00:24:11.292
We go out in pairs. sometimes alone.

151
00:24:12.293 --> 00:24:14.597
Their idea of combat
is tearing up the countryside...

152
00:24:14.640 --> 00:24:18.466
with heavy artillery
and millions of rounds.

153
00:24:18.510 --> 00:24:21.598
We'll wait days for one shot. one kill.

154
00:24:26.032 --> 00:24:28.468
Well. I guess it's a different
version of war.

155
00:24:30.119 --> 00:24:32.512
There's a lot of them
and just a few of us.

156
00:24:33.772 --> 00:24:35.425
What's that?

157
00:24:35.512 --> 00:24:38.818
Sometimes these shells
get nicks and burs on them.

158
00:24:38.904 --> 00:24:42.209
This little son of a bitch
will take your head of at 1.000 yards.

159
00:24:45.427 --> 00:24:47.904
Have you had a chance to look over
our operations plan?

160
00:24:49.167 --> 00:24:52.515
Yeah. I have.
but I wanna study it a little more.

161
00:24:52.602 --> 00:24:55.732
All right. Forget the specifics.
How about an overview?

162
00:24:55.776 --> 00:24:57.645
We'll get to that later.

163
00:24:57.732 --> 00:25:00.124
I have a few things I have to do.

164
00:25:02.515 --> 00:25:05.385
See you at 5- 0500.

165
00:25:05.472 --> 00:25:07.343
Having had.

166
00:25:07.385 --> 00:25:08.994
Having had what?

167
00:25:09.081 --> 00:25:10.821
Breakfast.

168
00:25:19.647 --> 00:25:21.648
This is Corporal Papich's gillie suit.

169
00:25:50.434 --> 00:25:54.218
Is that our ride?

170
00:25:54.304 --> 00:25:56.478
No. That's our ride.

171
00:25:58.131 --> 00:26:01.130
I thought this was a deep jungle
insertion. Don't we do that by chopper?

172
00:26:01.218 --> 00:26:03.436
Yeah. that's the usual S.O.P.

173
00:26:03.522 --> 00:26:06.132
But those asshole rotor heads
at battalion-

174
00:26:06.218 --> 00:26:08.479
they fucked with me
one time too many.

175
00:26:08.523 --> 00:26:10.480
We're gonna have to walk it in.

176
00:26:30.090 --> 00:26:31.482
My fiancée.

177
00:26:35.265 --> 00:26:36.874
You married?

178
00:26:52.920 --> 00:26:55.702
What's that?

179
00:26:55.745 --> 00:26:58.746
Got it out of the catalogue
when I was with D.C. SWAT.

180
00:26:59.702 --> 00:27:01.268
We called it "Gucciflage"

181
00:27:03.355 --> 00:27:06.094
- You gonna wear that?
- Yeah.

182
00:27:06.182 --> 00:27:07.834
Let me see it.

183
00:27:22.619 --> 00:27:26.141
- Nice shot!
- No room for Peter Pan on this hunt.

184
00:27:26.228 --> 00:27:29.576
You wear Corporal Papich's tree togs
that I gave you.

185
00:27:38.099 --> 00:27:40.273
What the hell are those for?

186
00:27:42.317 --> 00:27:43.577
Respect.

187
00:28:17.364 --> 00:28:20.278
Still think a chopper insertion would
have made a hell of a lot more sense.

188
00:28:20.364 --> 00:28:24.278
By the way. that was a hell of a shot
you made from a chopper.

189
00:28:28.539 --> 00:28:30.930
That's the sort of thing
myths are made of.

190
00:28:31.017 --> 00:28:32.887
Yeah. it was pretty unreal.

191
00:28:33.974 --> 00:28:35.410
Yeah.

192
00:28:42.454 --> 00:28:45.889
Roll down your sleeves. Miller.
We're going in the bush.

193
00:29:32.589 --> 00:29:34.547
What?

194
00:29:34.633 --> 00:29:36.112
What- I miss a spot?

195
00:29:37.939 --> 00:29:40.243
Come on. On your feet.

196
00:30:09.419 --> 00:30:11.551
I had a lot of SWAT training.
all right?

197
00:30:11.638 --> 00:30:15.204
Urban anti-terrorist tactics.
I've never actually done a creep.

198
00:30:16.725 --> 00:30:18.508
The army ever put you in the jungle?

199
00:30:21.596 --> 00:30:24.422
If you call deepest. darkest
North Carolina a jungle. yeah.

200
00:30:25.509 --> 00:30:27.596
You wanna survive this. right?

201
00:30:28.423 --> 00:30:30.205
You want an answer to that?

202
00:30:30.292 --> 00:30:32.989
Then if you do as I tell you.
to the letter-

203
00:30:34.162 --> 00:30:36.858
- I think you got a chance.
- Whoa! Hold on!

204
00:30:37.902 --> 00:30:40.685
You may have more experience than I do.
but with all due respect. gunny...

205
00:30:40.771 --> 00:30:42.206
this mission is N.S.C.

206
00:30:42.293 --> 00:30:45.337
Meaning I still have rank.
whether you see it or not.

207
00:30:46.686 --> 00:30:48.598
Sorry. but I don't have to take orders
from you.

208
00:30:48.686 --> 00:30:49.860
Fair enough.

209
00:30:51.208 --> 00:30:53.338
You want to take point?

210
00:30:57.643 --> 00:30:59.209
You're doing fine.

211
00:31:32.908 --> 00:31:34.605
I got it.

212
00:31:34.647 --> 00:31:37.125
- You sure?
- Yeah. Go ahead.

213
00:31:51.345 --> 00:31:53.736
Oh. fuck!

214
00:31:56.085 --> 00:31:58.476
Goddamn it!

215
00:31:59.651 --> 00:32:02.476
- You all right. son?
- Yeah.

216
00:32:02.520 --> 00:32:05.129
- Son of a bitch!
- Hey!

217
00:32:05.216 --> 00:32:07.652
Relax. You did okay.

218
00:32:07.738 --> 00:32:10.826
Thanks. You mean. there's a wrong way
to fall down a fucking mountain?

219
00:32:10.913 --> 00:32:14.305
Your weapon. Miller!
It's your life!

220
00:32:14.391 --> 00:32:17.261
You knew that. and you saved it.

221
00:32:21.827 --> 00:32:23.479
You're learning. son.

222
00:32:34.698 --> 00:32:37.698
Our drop point from the railway
was east.

223
00:32:37.785 --> 00:32:40.525
- Now. we're heading west here.
- I know that.

224
00:32:42.264 --> 00:32:43.786
That's not the plan.

225
00:32:43.829 --> 00:32:46.525
- The plan was no good.
- Now. what?

226
00:32:51.135 --> 00:32:52.657
We're changing directions.

227
00:32:52.699 --> 00:32:56.222
Okay. I was given
very specific orders...

228
00:32:56.308 --> 00:32:58.527
by the staff at the N.S.C.

229
00:32:58.614 --> 00:33:02.527
First it indicated a chopper insertion.
which we won't get into.

230
00:33:02.614 --> 00:33:06.441
But then we were supposed to head east.
you know? Due east?

231
00:33:06.485 --> 00:33:09.441
You think Washington knows
the best way to get through this jungle?

232
00:33:10.528 --> 00:33:14.007
You think they know which streams are
flooded. which trails are booby-trapped?

233
00:33:14.093 --> 00:33:16.399
What I know about this place. son...

234
00:33:16.442 --> 00:33:18.355
is because I'm here.

235
00:33:25.530 --> 00:33:27.226
Changing directions.

236
00:33:28.530 --> 00:33:30.922
Good. North.

237
00:33:36.618 --> 00:33:38.879
Holy shit.

238
00:33:38.923 --> 00:33:41.227
What the hell is that?

239
00:33:57.229 --> 00:33:59.316
"Hotel Europa."

240
00:34:00.751 --> 00:34:02.925
What kind of wacko builds a hotel
in the jungle?

241
00:34:22.450 --> 00:34:24.406
Sure is a hell of a lucky break for us.

242
00:34:32.145 --> 00:34:34.842
I got ammo and he's laughing?

243
00:34:36.930 --> 00:34:38.712
Ease up. young agent.

244
00:34:38.755 --> 00:34:41.190
They've been with us
since we left the train.

245
00:34:41.234 --> 00:34:44.800
If you drop the hammer on him. we'll be
dead before we can take ten steps.

246
00:35:11.063 --> 00:35:13.021
He wants my eyes?

247
00:35:15.281 --> 00:35:18.282
He means ante ojos.

248
00:35:19.368 --> 00:35:21.196
Your shooting glasses.

249
00:35:21.282 --> 00:35:22.935
Give them to him.

250
00:35:22.977 --> 00:35:24.935
- Why?
- Because he likes them.

251
00:35:24.979 --> 00:35:27.240
Fuck him!

252
00:35:27.327 --> 00:35:28.892
Fuck me.

253
00:35:30.631 --> 00:35:35.110
This area's swarming with rebel patrols.
These Indians can help us avoid them.

254
00:35:35.154 --> 00:35:36.675
Give him the glasses.

255
00:35:41.501 --> 00:35:42.937
May you go blind.

256
00:36:06.461 --> 00:36:08.548
Following these Indians
is fucking crazy.

257
00:36:08.592 --> 00:36:11.940
- Their agenda works with ours.
- What agenda?

258
00:36:12.028 --> 00:36:14.984
Do you see Cacique's hand-
the way it's cut up?

259
00:36:15.072 --> 00:36:18.071
The animal who did that
is el Cirujano.

260
00:36:18.157 --> 00:36:21.333
The Surgeon. He's headed this way.
and we're gonna take him out.

261
00:36:21.375 --> 00:36:23.768
In return. they'll lead us
passed the rebel patrols.

262
00:36:23.812 --> 00:36:25.768
We'll cut off hours on our time
to Sangre.

263
00:36:25.812 --> 00:36:28.811
Our mission isn't about assassinating
people for Indians!

264
00:36:28.899 --> 00:36:31.552
El Cirujano's listed
as a target of opportunity.

265
00:36:31.638 --> 00:36:34.029
That means. we see him.
we take him out.

266
00:36:34.117 --> 00:36:36.247
Listed where?
It's not in my orders. man.

267
00:36:36.290 --> 00:36:39.465
El Cirujano's gonna be at this
river up ahead. and Miller-

268
00:36:39.552 --> 00:36:41.727
You're the designated hitter on this.
So batter up.

269
00:36:41.813 --> 00:36:44.553
Hold on a second now!
I'm not buying into this.

270
00:36:44.597 --> 00:36:48.075
And I don't buy that you shot a man
from a moving helicopter.

271
00:36:49.075 --> 00:36:51.031
It's got nothing to do with anything!

272
00:36:51.118 --> 00:36:54.336
You're gonna look Cirujano in the eyes
and put a bullet through his heart...

273
00:36:54.380 --> 00:36:57.075
because until I see you kill a man
you're a liability to this mission!

274
00:36:57.119 --> 00:36:59.294
That's not my purpose here!

275
00:36:59.380 --> 00:37:02.556
Maybe. but when we get to Alvarez's
hacienda there's gonna be two targets!

276
00:37:02.642 --> 00:37:05.729
- Now. what?
- That's right.

277
00:37:05.816 --> 00:37:07.990
Intelligence changes all the time.

278
00:37:08.077 --> 00:37:11.642
Alvarez is setting up a meeting
with a man called Raoul Ochoa.

279
00:37:11.686 --> 00:37:14.209
He's a Colombian drug lord
that's financing the rebels.

280
00:37:14.295 --> 00:37:18.513
- We got a chance to get them both.
- Where does this information come from?

281
00:37:18.600 --> 00:37:20.601
Any new intelligence
has to come through me!

282
00:37:20.644 --> 00:37:22.340
A local contact- Father Ruiz.

283
00:37:22.426 --> 00:37:24.601
He's a priest in the village of Sangre.

284
00:37:24.688 --> 00:37:27.383
They'll give us specifics on the meeting
when we get there.

285
00:37:41.994 --> 00:37:45.038
Wind coming off the water at 3:00.

286
00:37:45.124 --> 00:37:47.473
One click right.

287
00:37:49.038 --> 00:37:51.126
Make that two clicks.

288
00:38:01.519 --> 00:38:03.953
Which one is he?
I can't tell who he is.

289
00:38:04.997 --> 00:38:07.955
He's the baseball fan.

290
00:38:08.997 --> 00:38:10.649
He's a fucking American!

291
00:38:10.693 --> 00:38:13.128
He's a fucking spook.
Ex-CIA.

292
00:38:13.172 --> 00:38:15.216
I met him once up in El Salvador.

293
00:38:16.433 --> 00:38:18.955
Now he's an enforcer
for the cocaine monkeys.

294
00:38:19.042 --> 00:38:20.781
I'll take out the lieutenant.

295
00:38:20.868 --> 00:38:23.608
You concentrate on him.

296
00:38:23.651 --> 00:38:27.042
Now put a fucking bullet
through his heart!

297
00:38:31.348 --> 00:38:33.392
Do it! Feel the rush!

298
00:38:55.829 --> 00:38:57.264
Breathe.

299
00:39:10.787 --> 00:39:12.700
Nail that motherfucker now!

300
00:39:49.052 --> 00:39:50.965
What the hell did you just do. sniper?

301
00:39:52.227 --> 00:39:54.488
I just wanted to show you
that I owned that situation.

302
00:39:54.574 --> 00:39:57.836
Bullshit! You fired a spoiler.

303
00:39:57.923 --> 00:40:00.097
You saw him go down.
He's dead!

304
00:40:00.184 --> 00:40:02.010
I didn't see shit!
I didn't see him hit!

305
00:40:02.054 --> 00:40:04.227
For Christ sake! You gave him
a warning shot!

306
00:40:04.315 --> 00:40:05.837
I hit him!

307
00:40:05.923 --> 00:40:07.924
I had him in my sights.
no doubt about it.

308
00:40:09.880 --> 00:40:11.402
You'd better be right.

309
00:40:12.621 --> 00:40:14.316
From now on...

310
00:40:14.360 --> 00:40:16.795
one shot. one kill.

311
00:40:16.839 --> 00:40:19.752
No exceptions. Do you understand?

312
00:40:55.843 --> 00:40:57.843
What? Now they blame us for this?

313
00:41:05.018 --> 00:41:07.844
But they sure as hell
ain't gonna help us.

314
00:42:36.984 --> 00:42:38.681
Patrols.

315
00:43:23.077 --> 00:43:25.077
You really get off on this shit.
don't you?

316
00:43:26.251 --> 00:43:28.816
It's just a job.
I don't think about it much.

317
00:43:28.903 --> 00:43:30.904
So that's the secret:
not thinking.

318
00:43:36.077 --> 00:43:37.774
What are you doing here?

319
00:43:37.861 --> 00:43:40.470
This assignment was supposed to be
a piece of cake.

320
00:43:40.558 --> 00:43:43.513
You're in. you're out. You go back home.
You reap the rewards.

321
00:43:43.601 --> 00:43:45.601
Washington brass loves this shit.

322
00:43:46.688 --> 00:43:49.732
They never said anything about
a goddamn jungle creep. that's for sure.

323
00:43:49.775 --> 00:43:52.254
Yeah. well. Those guys wouldn't.

324
00:43:52.341 --> 00:43:54.646
It seems so far away.

325
00:43:55.516 --> 00:43:58.385
- What?
- My life.

326
00:44:01.255 --> 00:44:04.864
I read your dossier before I came.
You had 74 confirmed kills.

327
00:44:06.778 --> 00:44:08.603
It's not about numbers.

328
00:44:08.691 --> 00:44:12.169
The only one that really mattered
was the first one.

329
00:44:12.256 --> 00:44:14.170
That was the toughest one
for you. right?

330
00:44:15.256 --> 00:44:16.823
First one?

331
00:44:18.039 --> 00:44:19.301
Yeah.

332
00:44:21.171 --> 00:44:23.997
Seventy-four. that's...

333
00:44:24.041 --> 00:44:25.997
a lot of faces to carry around.

334
00:44:27.084 --> 00:44:30.085
Yeah. well.

335
00:44:30.127 --> 00:44:32.737
You put them in the back of your mind...

336
00:44:33.780 --> 00:44:35.564
and you just keep on going.

337
00:44:35.650 --> 00:44:38.172
Until they decide
not to stay in the back of your mind.

338
00:44:40.130 --> 00:44:42.521
You may find this hard to believe...

339
00:44:42.608 --> 00:44:45.303
but I'd take a nice office
on the Hill over this shit any day.

340
00:44:45.391 --> 00:44:48.261
Sitting in an office.
giving other men orders to kill...

341
00:44:48.304 --> 00:44:50.826
ain't no different than putting
a bullet in a man's heart.

342
00:44:50.914 --> 00:44:53.827
Let me tell you something.

343
00:44:53.870 --> 00:44:56.741
It's the same goddamn thing.

344
00:45:02.870 --> 00:45:05.349
- You hear that?
- An AK.

345
00:45:06.480 --> 00:45:09.089
- I know that hammer recoil.
- Yeah.

346
00:45:09.176 --> 00:45:11.785
And I think I know
who that single shot is.

347
00:45:11.829 --> 00:45:13.089
He's behind us.

348
00:45:39.527 --> 00:45:41.267
Who is this guy?

349
00:45:41.354 --> 00:45:43.527
I think he's the guy
that killed Papich.

350
00:45:43.615 --> 00:45:46.267
It ain't the first time
he's been on my trail.

351
00:45:46.310 --> 00:45:49.963
He's a Panamanian I trained.

352
00:45:50.051 --> 00:45:52.398
His name's DeSilva.

353
00:45:52.442 --> 00:45:54.399
Now he's a fucking mercenary.

354
00:46:15.662 --> 00:46:17.663
This is ridiculous. I can't sleep here.

355
00:46:18.793 --> 00:46:20.706
It's a good spot.

356
00:46:20.793 --> 00:46:25.098
Stagnant. Liver flukes.
leaches. malaria.

357
00:46:25.142 --> 00:46:28.142
He'd never think anybody'd be
stupid enough to hide here.

358
00:46:28.186 --> 00:46:30.664
Except us.

359
00:46:30.750 --> 00:46:34.055
Just take your horse pill.

360
00:46:34.142 --> 00:46:35.795
And don't take a piss.

361
00:46:35.882 --> 00:46:38.621
Bugs will swarm
right up through your dick.

362
00:46:38.707 --> 00:46:40.665
Good night.

363
00:47:30.540 --> 00:47:32.192
Tough. huh?

364
00:47:42.759 --> 00:47:46.238
He's there. and he's out of range.
damn it!

365
00:47:46.324 --> 00:47:48.934
I'm looking right at the ridge
that we came over.

366
00:47:49.021 --> 00:47:50.846
I don't see a damn thing.

367
00:47:50.933 --> 00:47:53.804
That's because he's smarter than you.
Come over here.

368
00:48:05.674 --> 00:48:08.588
Glance down to the bottom of the finger.

369
00:48:09.587 --> 00:48:11.936
Sweep up to your left
at 11:00.

370
00:48:12.023 --> 00:48:14.372
- Halfway.
- Got him.

371
00:48:16.023 --> 00:48:18.111
Heading west.

372
00:48:18.198 --> 00:48:19.894
Lost us.

373
00:48:19.980 --> 00:48:23.068
Wrong. He's just doing
what he was trained to do.

374
00:48:25.677 --> 00:48:28.503
He's circling our flank.
coming around us.

375
00:48:28.547 --> 00:48:30.330
Gaining some ground.

376
00:48:31.329 --> 00:48:33.591
He'll be waiting for us somewhere.

377
00:48:36.374 --> 00:48:39.461
He'll know exactly where we are.

378
00:48:39.549 --> 00:48:41.939
We have to take him out.

379
00:48:59.420 --> 00:49:01.158
Taking a break?

380
00:49:11.291 --> 00:49:13.291
Makes it sensitive.

381
00:49:13.335 --> 00:49:15.334
Marries my finger to the trigger-break.

382
00:49:15.378 --> 00:49:17.857
What are you gonna do. a pedicure next?

383
00:49:20.553 --> 00:49:23.336
I guess some men are born to this work
and others aren't.

384
00:49:25.075 --> 00:49:27.119
It may be your career choice
but it ain't mine.

385
00:49:27.206 --> 00:49:30.989
This career chooses the man.
Ain't the other way around.

386
00:49:31.076 --> 00:49:32.989
Well. like I said-

387
00:49:33.076 --> 00:49:36.033
- I have other plans.
- Yeah?

388
00:49:36.120 --> 00:49:38.816
I had plans. Still do.

389
00:49:42.686 --> 00:49:47.034
- What is it?
- I'm working on something back home.

390
00:49:49.078 --> 00:49:51.035
Where are you from?

391
00:49:51.077 --> 00:49:54.035
Montana. Boseman.

392
00:49:54.079 --> 00:49:55.773
No shit? I went to university there.

393
00:49:59.556 --> 00:50:02.384
Miller. don't jerk me off.
I'm not in the mood.

394
00:50:02.427 --> 00:50:05.427
I'm not. Freshman and sophomore year.

395
00:50:05.471 --> 00:50:07.428
I would have stayed longer
but skiing killed my grades.

396
00:50:10.558 --> 00:50:12.993
I'll be damned.

397
00:50:15.472 --> 00:50:18.125
You wouldn't happen to know
a little town called Livingston?

398
00:50:18.168 --> 00:50:19.429
Sure.

399
00:50:21.648 --> 00:50:24.168
Well...

400
00:50:24.256 --> 00:50:27.691
there's a stream nearby.
up in the hills.

401
00:50:27.777 --> 00:50:30.735
It's. I don't know. What- three clicks
east of the interstate.

402
00:50:30.778 --> 00:50:36.082
If you follow that.
you come to this rock basin.

403
00:50:36.171 --> 00:50:38.953
Like a quarry pit. but not as deep.

404
00:50:38.996 --> 00:50:40.736
I found that when I was a kid.

405
00:50:40.823 --> 00:50:44.432
Anyway. it's fed by
a tributary of the Madison.

406
00:50:44.476 --> 00:50:47.433
And it's the best damned
steelhead fishing in the world.

407
00:50:47.476 --> 00:50:49.998
I plan to go back there and-

408
00:50:51.477 --> 00:50:54.085
I don't know.
Start a little fishing camp.

409
00:50:54.172 --> 00:50:56.650
Guide operation. Whatever.

410
00:50:57.650 --> 00:50:59.434
When's the last time you were there?

411
00:51:01.826 --> 00:51:03.782
Couple years ago.

412
00:51:05.086 --> 00:51:07.087
Damn it- "couple years ago."

413
00:51:07.174 --> 00:51:09.088
That whole area was leveled
seven years ago!

414
00:51:09.174 --> 00:51:11.782
They got a high school there now!
Your pond is buried.

415
00:51:11.826 --> 00:51:13.305
It's a tennis court!

416
00:51:17.871 --> 00:51:19.696
We're not talking about the same place.

417
00:51:20.958 --> 00:51:23.959
You know we are.
whether you admit it or not.

418
00:51:25.480 --> 00:51:27.612
Killing's all you got. isn't it?

419
00:51:56.266 --> 00:51:58.180
What is it?

420
00:52:19.356 --> 00:52:21.573
Something's wrong here.

421
00:53:54.584 --> 00:53:56.192
God.

422
00:53:58.671 --> 00:54:00.803
What kind of-

423
00:54:01.889 --> 00:54:03.846
Who would do something like that?

424
00:54:07.064 --> 00:54:09.543
I'd say the man you had
dead in your sights did this.

425
00:54:09.629 --> 00:54:11.848
You don't know it was el Cirujano.

426
00:54:11.934 --> 00:54:15.326
Probably Alvarez's men. They probably
found out what the priest was doing.

427
00:54:15.413 --> 00:54:19.065
He must have told them everything.
They're going to be waiting for us.

428
00:54:19.109 --> 00:54:20.978
Maybe.

429
00:54:21.066 --> 00:54:24.414
But if he told them everything.
why didn't they hit us here?

430
00:54:44.199 --> 00:54:46.285
The hacienda's only three clicks away.

431
00:54:47.590 --> 00:54:49.721
We should make our shots easy at dawn.

432
00:54:49.808 --> 00:54:51.940
What? This mission is over.

433
00:54:53.417 --> 00:54:56.765
Our contact is dead! All we do now
is get the hell out of here!

434
00:54:56.809 --> 00:54:59.722
I've never turned back on a mission
in my life. and I ain't gonna start now.

435
00:54:59.810 --> 00:55:03.158
Such gung-ho bullshit! Without the
specifics. it's a suicide mission!

436
00:55:03.245 --> 00:55:07.245
They all are! I wouldn't be out here
unless I was ready to die!

437
00:55:07.332 --> 00:55:09.419
We've got our location.
We've got our targets.

438
00:55:09.506 --> 00:55:13.289
- And we got a time frame!
- You're out of your fucking mind!

439
00:55:13.332 --> 00:55:15.289
I'm not going!

440
00:55:25.160 --> 00:55:28.291
I've had enough of your mewling!
Shut your fucking mouth!

441
00:55:28.378 --> 00:55:30.248
- I'm not going with you!
- The hell your aren't!

442
00:55:30.334 --> 00:55:31.814
You have no choice!

443
00:55:33.987 --> 00:55:36.987
- It'll never work.
- We're going where they won't expect us.

444
00:56:16.123 --> 00:56:19.297
Jar head. Fucking flag-top lifer.

445
00:56:57.432 --> 00:56:59.997
We camp here.

446
00:57:00.085 --> 00:57:03.259
We'll make our final approach
to the hacienda at dawn.

447
00:57:03.345 --> 00:57:05.258
Wait a minute. okay?

448
00:57:05.346 --> 00:57:08.606
Now. at the village you said we were
three clicks away from the hacienda.

449
00:57:08.694 --> 00:57:11.911
That is three clicks.
We've been walking for miles.

450
00:57:11.999 --> 00:57:14.912
We don't walk in straight lines.

451
00:57:14.999 --> 00:57:17.738
Get some sleep.
I'll take the first watch.

452
00:57:18.651 --> 00:57:20.869
Move out at 0400.

453
00:57:23.173 --> 00:57:25.044
You sleep here.

454
01:00:49.240 --> 01:00:51.763
Son of a bitch! You used me as bait?

455
01:00:54.676 --> 01:00:56.676
You were never really in any danger.

456
01:01:26.594 --> 01:01:28.549
We're about 100 yards out.

457
01:01:28.593 --> 01:01:31.420
This is our rendezvous point.

458
01:01:31.507 --> 01:01:34.072
If I don't show. you cross country
to the nearest river...

459
01:01:34.116 --> 01:01:36.072
follow it downstream to the coast.

460
01:01:36.159 --> 01:01:37.334
Whatever.

461
01:02:00.684 --> 01:02:03.075
Hacienda. 12:00.

462
01:02:05.858 --> 01:02:07.641
The most logical position would be...

463
01:02:07.728 --> 01:02:11.771
to take our shots from that tree line
over there.

464
01:02:11.859 --> 01:02:14.338
But they're going to be expecting that.

465
01:02:14.424 --> 01:02:17.991
So somehow. we gotta get in the clear
to make our shots.

466
01:02:18.903 --> 01:02:20.860
When Ochoa arrives...

467
01:02:20.947 --> 01:02:24.557
I figure we got ten seconds
after they greet...

468
01:02:24.643 --> 01:02:26.296
and then we drop them.

469
01:02:26.382 --> 01:02:28.600
Then we gotta fire
our shots simultaneously...

470
01:02:28.644 --> 01:02:31.383
or they're gonna vector in
on our positions.

471
01:02:34.687 --> 01:02:37.122
Here's Ochoa. He's yours.

472
01:02:49.428 --> 01:02:53.081
There's a clear shot from that
metal utility shed. You got coverage.

473
01:02:53.167 --> 01:02:54.951
That's your position.

474
01:02:55.038 --> 01:02:57.516
I'll be on the other side
of the village.

475
01:02:57.604 --> 01:02:59.864
We'll both be...

476
01:02:59.952 --> 01:03:01.517
thousand yards out.

477
01:03:03.343 --> 01:03:05.257
You listening. Miller?

478
01:03:08.300 --> 01:03:09.735
Get below.

479
01:03:23.259 --> 01:03:26.215
There better not be any doubt
about your shot this time.

480
01:03:26.302 --> 01:03:28.651
One shot. One kill.

481
01:03:28.693 --> 01:03:31.607
This ain't a fucking game out here!

482
01:03:31.651 --> 01:03:35.304
- You blow it. and I'll tear-
- You'll what?

483
01:03:35.390 --> 01:03:38.391
You'll kill me?
Come on. Say it. Beckett.

484
01:03:38.434 --> 01:03:40.260
You just get it right.

485
01:05:32.186 --> 01:05:34.709
Son of a bitch!

486
01:06:13.930 --> 01:06:16.191
You lying bastard!

487
01:06:30.149 --> 01:06:32.280
Fucking truck's blocking my shot.

488
01:07:06.415 --> 01:07:08.197
What are you doing?

489
01:10:56.484 --> 01:10:58.180
Where is he?

490
01:11:08.530 --> 01:11:10.400
Oh. shit. Miller!

491
01:11:14.139 --> 01:11:16.270
You're out in the open!

492
01:11:28.271 --> 01:11:29.532
Fuck.

493
01:11:35.315 --> 01:11:37.359
Shit! Miller. someone's seen you.

494
01:11:52.752 --> 01:11:55.317
What are you doing?

495
01:12:30.278 --> 01:12:32.713
Alvarez.

496
01:12:42.670 --> 01:12:43.932
Ochoa.

497
01:12:52.281 --> 01:12:53.759
Ten...

498
01:12:53.846 --> 01:12:55.281
nine...

499
01:12:55.367 --> 01:12:58.585
eight. seven-

500
01:13:05.021 --> 01:13:06.195
Lady. move!

501
01:13:09.325 --> 01:13:11.327
One.

502
01:13:13.761 --> 01:13:16.152
One. Beckett! One!

503
01:16:38.045 --> 01:16:39.959
Oh. shit.

504
01:16:55.744 --> 01:16:57.570
- Did you get Ochoa?
- Yes. I got Ochoa.

505
01:16:57.614 --> 01:16:59.527
What happened to you?
What were you doing in that barn?

506
01:16:59.613 --> 01:17:03.222
It doesn't matter. We gotta try and get
back and try and hit Alvarez after dark.

507
01:17:03.266 --> 01:17:07.570
What. another shot? Are you crazy?
I got my kill. I'm out of this mission!

508
01:17:07.657 --> 01:17:10.136
- There's still two targets left-
- You're the one who fucked up.

509
01:17:10.223 --> 01:17:12.962
You son of a bitch.
He had the drop on you.

510
01:17:13.050 --> 01:17:15.441
He had you in his crosshairs.
and I took him out.

511
01:17:15.529 --> 01:17:18.311
Fuck you! I'm not ending up
on your fucking key chain. Beckett.

512
01:19:37.806 --> 01:19:39.936
Give it up. Miller!

513
01:19:52.720 --> 01:19:54.937
You're losing it!
Pull it together.

514
01:20:11.635 --> 01:20:13.461
Beautiful.

515
01:21:41.298 --> 01:21:44.689
Miller. it's over.

516
01:21:44.776 --> 01:21:47.864
I'm out of bullets.
Do it.

517
01:21:51.343 --> 01:21:53.778
So come on and shoot me already.

518
01:21:54.865 --> 01:21:56.778
You feel the rush?

519
01:21:58.648 --> 01:22:00.822
I felt it.

520
01:22:00.909 --> 01:22:03.257
I felt it when I had you
in my crosshairs.

521
01:22:03.343 --> 01:22:05.083
After you pull the trigger...

522
01:22:06.735 --> 01:22:09.388
when the rush is over...

523
01:22:11.563 --> 01:22:15.432
it hurts. doesn't it?

524
01:22:16.519 --> 01:22:19.477
The hurt you're feeling now
ain't the worst pain.

525
01:22:21.694 --> 01:22:23.651
The worst thing...

526
01:22:26.086 --> 01:22:28.216
is not feeling the hurt anymore.

527
01:22:30.912 --> 01:22:32.826
You'll get past this.

528
01:22:34.391 --> 01:22:36.348
You'll get by.

529
01:22:38.261 --> 01:22:40.783
Hey...

530
01:22:40.871 --> 01:22:43.261
you can still go home.

531
01:22:58.002 --> 01:22:59.960
Get out of here.
I'll cover you.

532
01:23:08.872 --> 01:23:12.569
Son. I'm getting you out of here.
Now go.

533
01:23:19.179 --> 01:23:22.265
I'II be right behind you.
Move it!

534
01:26:23.721 --> 01:26:25.374
Tell me who you are.

535
01:26:28.852 --> 01:26:30.506
Lee Harvey Oswald.

536
01:26:38.941 --> 01:26:40.680
We've been looking for you.

537
01:26:45.377 --> 01:26:47.724
You've hurt our cause.

538
01:26:47.811 --> 01:26:50.029
Fuck you and fuck your cause.

539
01:26:58.421 --> 01:27:03.074
Well. all things come to he who waits.
Right. Beckett?

540
01:27:06.336 --> 01:27:08.119
Long time no see.

541
01:27:08.161 --> 01:27:10.119
See if there's any others.

542
01:27:11.727 --> 01:27:14.988
Beckett and I are gonna have a long
talk. We'll hear about everything.

543
01:27:39.383 --> 01:27:41.426
Everyone back to the hacienda.

544
01:27:53.384 --> 01:27:55.210
Feel the trigger. sniper.

545
01:27:56.428 --> 01:27:58.081
It'll be the last time.

546
01:28:17.604 --> 01:28:19.300
Where'd you leave your partner?

547
01:28:33.258 --> 01:28:37.562
Now. you targeted Ochoa.
a Colombian civilian.

548
01:28:37.651 --> 01:28:40.476
Is the U.S. military now moving
against the Colombian cartel?

549
01:28:55.652 --> 01:29:00.131
Thomas Beckett.
master gunnery sergeant...

550
01:29:00.218 --> 01:29:03.176
United States Marine Corps.

551
01:29:17.045 --> 01:29:19.264
I like your dedication. Beckett.

552
01:29:21.002 --> 01:29:22.568
It's a challenge.

553
01:30:49.318 --> 01:30:52.143
Wake up!
Don't die on me yet. Beckett.

554
01:30:52.231 --> 01:30:54.492
I'm just starting to have fun.

555
01:31:16.973 --> 01:31:18.189
Wait.

556
01:31:21.365 --> 01:31:23.191
Wait?

557
01:31:25.452 --> 01:31:30.757
Please.
One shot. two kills.

558
01:31:30.801 --> 01:31:33.496
One shot...

559
01:31:33.584 --> 01:31:35.497
two kills.

560
01:31:36.802 --> 01:31:39.192
A man...

561
01:31:39.280 --> 01:31:41.194
in the organization-

562
01:31:42.801 --> 01:31:45.759
- What?
- A man-

563
01:31:49.063 --> 01:31:50.759
What?

564
01:31:51.760 --> 01:31:54.151
Move.

565
01:32:46.766 --> 01:32:48.635
We gotta go one click.
Can you make it?

566
01:32:48.679 --> 01:32:51.027
- Yeah.
- All right.

567
01:32:51.114 --> 01:32:52.853
Let's go.

568
01:32:54.115 --> 01:32:57.637
One minute to rendezvous.
They better be there.

569
01:32:57.724 --> 01:33:00.115
Take her down.

570
01:33:22.379 --> 01:33:23.988
Beckett. go.

571
01:33:24.074 --> 01:33:28.075
- Give me that rifle. I'll cover you.
- Go on! That's an order.

572
01:34:45.040 --> 01:34:46.736
Let's go!

573
01:35:10.000 --> 01:35:12.175
There's always Montana.
